value.0: Whut?
Daun' hurt meh! Ah hain't dun nuthin'!
Ah gaut wurk t' de. Theh gaunna beat meh if'n ah doesn' de eht.
Dunneh. Ah daun' knauw nuthin' 'baut thet. Ah daun' wanneh gau inna dungeons.
Dunneh. Ah stays aweh when theh caum by. Ah daun' wanneh gau inna dungeons.
Dunneh. Ah stays aweh when heh caum by. Ah daun' wanneh gau inna dungeons.
'Is beh th' raud t' th' est.
Ther beh speerits an' ghoosts an' sech aboot. Ah nivver gaun ther. Ah dun wanna die.

Mmm. Ther beh a haurse speerit whut haunts th' raud a' nicht, black as th' grehve an' breathin' fahr, 'tis said. Him whut sees it afar gaun' die wi'in th' tenday. Him whut sees it oop near git dragged t' th' hells t' be eht, ayup.
Ayup. Ol' dead Cutter Fahan beh hauntin' his house wi' his big axe. Heh cut yeh up bad an drag yeh t' th' hells t' eht yeh if'n heh catch yeh!
'Is beh th' raud t' th' west.
Inna muntins.
'Is beh Os'dur.
Whut?
Allus haungreh.
Ehf ye eht th' fruit, eht mehk yeh mad. An' then yeh dies, haurtin' bad isside.
Ayup. Ehven th' leaves is haurt yeh.
Theh says th' Axe's laydeh daun' plantid eht, menneh yehrs agau. But ah dun lahk it.
Hello, boy.
Don't worry, son. I just wanted to ask you a few questions.
All right. I don't want to get you in trouble. Bye, now.
Is there any work to be had around here?
Who's this Magnus guy I keep hearing about?
The guards keep things on a pretty tight leash around here.
Good plan. Thanks for the advice. I think I should be going now.
That sounds prudent. Can I ask you something else?
Do you think I could arrange to see the Axe himself?
What lies to the east of here?
The road, yes. To the east, got it. Is there anything else you can tell me about it?
Thanks for the information, boy.
Sounds like a good place to keep away from. Can you tell me anything else?
Spirits?
Thanks. Good bye now.
Seems there are lots of things around here that'll eat you. Can I ask you something else?
You said something about ghosts?
Ghosts?
Thanks. Good bye now.
That's pretty scary. Can I ask you something else?
You mentioned spirits?
What lies to the west of here?
I see. I'll be going now.
I see. Can I ask you something else?
I see. Do you know where it goes?
I can see that. I guess I'd better ask someone else, then.
I can see that. Can I ask you something else?
Can you tell me a bit about this town?
Uh, yeah, I know that already. Can you tell me anything else?
Everybody seems hungry here. Why's that?
I see fruit up in the tree, there. Can't you eat that?
It's poisonous, you mean?
That's interesting. But I'd better be going now.
I see. Can I ask you something else?
It certainly sounds dangerous. Why don't they cut it down, then?
What's this big pink tree over here?
That's interesting. But I'd better be going now.
I see. Can I ask you something else?
You don't -like- it? Why?
